        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(openai): bound JSON/text response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nBound OpenAI provider HTTP response reads to prevent unbounded buffering from\nuntrusted upstream JSON/text bodies.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `extensions/openai/embedding-batch.ts` | Use `readProviderJsonResponse` for batch status JSON (1 MiB cap). File content reader left unbounded to avoid Batch output ceiling risk. |\n| `extensions/openai/openai-chatgpt-oauth-flow.runtime.ts` | Cap token endpoint response body at first read in `postTokenForm` via `readResponseWithLimit` (must use raw reader to re-wrap body in `new Response()`). Downstream `response.json()` is bounded by the already-capped body. |\n| `extensions/openai/realtime-provider-shared.ts` | Use `readProviderJsonResponse` for client secret JSON (1 MiB cap). |\n| `extensions/openai/image-generation-provider.ts` | Intentionally unchanged — already uses `readProviderJsonResponse` with configurable `maxBytes`. |\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP proof: bounded reader cancels oversized stream at 1 MiB\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_bounded_json.mts\n\n[proof] real server, cap=1048576 bytes, would-stream≈67108864 bytes\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: server sent ≈ cap bytes, not ~64 MiB :: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly :: status=ok id=batch-1\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap :: buffered=33554457 bytes (> 1048576)\n\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\n### Design: shared provider readers where applicable\n\n- JSON paths use `readProviderJsonResponse` (shared provider contract with consistent\n  overflow and malformed-response labels) where the caller consumes parsed JSON\n- Only `postTokenForm` uses raw `readResponseWithLimit` because it must re-wrap\n  the bounded body in `new Response()` for downstream callers\n- Batch output file content intentionally left unbounded to avoid the output ceiling\n  risk flagged by review\n\n_AI-assisted._",
